    <fr:title text="Relational extensionality">Relational extensionality</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> be two sets, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R,S\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>. Then we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R=S]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall {a\in  A}\mathpunct {.} \forall {b\in  B}\mathpunct {.} a\mathrel {R}b\Longleftrightarrow  a\mathrel {S}b]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We recall that <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is nothing more than a subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex>. By the axiom of extensionality, two subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex> are equal if and only if they contain precisely the same elements.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
