            <fr:title text="Partial functional extensionality">Partial functional extensionality</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f,g\colon  A\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } B]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="/jms-00K7/" title="Partial function" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00K7/" display-uri="jms-00K7" type="local">partial functions</fr:link>. We have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f=g]]></fr:tex> if and only if for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/jms-00KA/" title="Values of partial functions" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KA/" display-uri="jms-00KA" type="local">defined</fr:link> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> is defined at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and, moreover, the <fr:link href="/jms-00KA/" title="Values of partial functions" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KA/" display-uri="jms-00KA" type="local">value</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> is the same as the <fr:link href="/jms-00KA/" title="Values of partial functions" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KA/" display-uri="jms-00KA" type="local">value</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>:</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 f=g
 \Longleftrightarrow 
 \forall  a\in  A\mathpunct {.}
 {\mathopen {}\left (
  f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow } \Leftrightarrow  g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }
 \right )\mathclose {}}
 \land 
 f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} = g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}
]]></fr:tex>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>One direction is trivial. In the other direction, we assume
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   \forall  a\in  A\mathpunct {.}
   {\mathopen {}\left (
    f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow } \Leftrightarrow  g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }
   \right )\mathclose {}}
   \land 
   f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} = g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}
  ]]></fr:tex>
  to deduce <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f=g]]></fr:tex>. By <fr:link href="/jms-00IM/" title="Relational extensionality" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IM/" display-uri="jms-00IM" type="local">relational extensionality</fr:link>, it suffices to show
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   \forall  a\in  A\mathpunct {.}
   \forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.}
   a\mathrel {f}b \Longleftrightarrow  a\mathrel {g}b.
  ]]></fr:tex></html:p>

 <html:p>Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex>, we assume <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {f} b]]></fr:tex> to prove <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {g}b]]></fr:tex>. By assumption, we deduce <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }]]></fr:tex>, so there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b'=g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {g}b']]></fr:tex>. By our other assumption, we know that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, so we conclude <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {g}b]]></fr:tex>. The other direction works the same way.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
